==English==
[[File:Achillea millefolium 20041012 2574.jpg|thumb|a '''yarrow''' plant ''Achillea millefolium'']]
===Pronunciation===
* {{a|RP}} {{IPA|en|/ˈjæɹəʊ/}}
* {{audio|en|LL-Q1860 (eng)-Vealhurl-yarrow.wav|Audio (RP)}}
* {{a|GA}} {{IPA|en|/ˈjɛɹoʊ/}}
* {{rhymes|en|æɹəʊ|s=2}}
===Etymology 1===
From {{inh|en|enm|ȝarowe}}, {{m|enm|yarowe}}, {{m|enm|yarwe}}, from {{inh|en|ang|ġearwe}}, from {{inh|en|gmw-pro|*garwu||yarrow, yarrow-like herbs}}. Cognate with {{cog|nl|gerw|t=yarrow}} and {{cog|de|Schafgarbe|(Schaf-)garbe}}.
====Noun====
{{en-noun|-|s}}
# Any of several [[pungent]] [[Eurasian]] and [[North American]] [[herb]]s, of the [[genus]] {{m|mul|Achillea}}, used in traditional [[herbal]] [[medicine]].
# [[common yarrow|Common yarrow]], {{m|mul|Achillea millefolium}}, the [[type species]] of the genus.
#* '''1612''', {{w|Michael Drayton}}, {{w|Poly-Olbion}} song{{nbsp}}13 p.{{nbsp}}218[http://poly-olbion.exeter.ac.uk/the-text/full-text/song-13/]:
#*: The '''Yarrow''', where-with-all he stops the wound-made gore:
#* {{quote-book|en|1979|Victor Kaplan|The Woman who Gathered Yarrow; The Box; Miss Vesey's Other Leg||11|“Oh, '''yarrow'''! This is it,” she said, extracting a single long stemmed ferny grass with clusters of small white flowers from the bouquet in her hand.|isbn=9780915306183}}
